# State Engine & OWASP-Aligned Rules

## Purpose

The State Engine evaluates engagement context and produces **next-step suggestions**.

## Design Constraints

* Deterministic
* Read-only (no state mutation)
* Transparent and debuggable

## Methodology Alignment (OWASP WSTG)

| Internal Phase    | OWASP WSTG           |
| ----------------- | -------------------- |
| Recon             | WSTG-INFO            |
| Enumeration       | WSTG-CONF, WSTG-IDNT |
| Exploitation      | WSTG-INPV, AUTHZ     |
| Post-Exploitation | WSTG-BUSL, IMPACT    |

## Rule Characteristics

* Phase-scoped
* Condition-based
* Suggestion-only

## Rule Inputs

* Current phase
* Services
* Ports
* Findings tags

## Rule Outputs

* Suggested techniques
* Notes or warnings

## Safety Guarantees

* No auto phase changes
* No command execution
* No vulnerability assumptions
